Use COE file to define row permutations
Use COE file to define column permutations

spirit:component.spirit:description: The Xilinx Interleaver/De-interleaver module is a high speed, compact design and implements either the Forney Convolutional or Rectangular Block type architecture. For the Convolutional type, the number of branches and branch lengths are parameterizable. For the Rectangular Block type the number of rows and columns is parameterizable or run-time variable. Row and column permutations are also supported. The core supports a symbol size ranging from 1 to 256 bits.
